// Conformance case: Stable "String" primitive type + the `\n`, `\t`,
// `\\`, `\"` escapes from "String/byte literal escape syntax"
// (STABILITY.md § Feature Stability › Stable).
//
// NOTE: `\xNN` / `\u{NNNN}` are listed in the same STABILITY.md bullet
// but are only decoded by the byte-literal (`b"..."`) path today, not
// plain string literals — both backends agree on that (no parity gap),
// so this case sticks to the escapes plain strings actually support.
// See the doc/reality gap noted in docs/CONFORMANCE.md.
fn main() {
    println("line1\nline2");
    println("a\tb");
    println("back\\slash");
    println("quote\"inside");
    println(type_of("hi"));
}
main();
